學習規範 Course Policy
	    1. Please check Moodle regularly. Announcements and course materials will be posted on Moodle. It is recommended that you set your Moodle email to your primary email address. Announcements will also be sent to your email via Moodle.
2. Student attendance will be greatly valued. Random roll calls will be made during the class.
3. Class participation is vital. If you volunteer to speak or answer the questions, extra points will be given to you. However, if you did not participate in the group/pair discussions, your participation grades will be adversely affected.
4. Makeup quizzes, midterms, and finals, which should be made WITHIN one week after the official tests, will NOT be given unless you show an official document from NCKU, proving your leave of absence.
5. Other detailed announcements will be made during the class.      

